[name]
check_snmp_int

[info]
The plugin checks host interface state and usage.

[why]
For example to get notified if you suddenly have strange traffic pattern in you network, eg virus attack or if an interface or to help you locate network problems.

[how]
The plugin check interface operationnal status over SNMP using the MIB-II table.

[platforms]
Not platform depended.

[categories]
SNMP, Networking

[support]
5

[tags]
network interface, status, snmp
